{{use American English|date=August 2013}}
[[File:Map of the United States with flags.svg|thumb|right|400px|Map showing the current flags of the 50 states]]

The '''[[flag]]s of the [[United States|U.S.]] [[U.S. state|state]]s, [[Territories of the United States|territories]], and [[federal district]]''' exhibit a variety of regional influences and local histories, as well as different styles and design principles. Nonetheless, the majority of the states' flags share the same design pattern consisting of the [[List of U.S. state, district, and territorial seals|state seal]] superimposed on a monochrome background, commonly every different shade of blue.

The most recent current state flag is that of [[Utah]] (February 16, 2011), while the most recent current territorial flag is that of the [[Northern Mariana Islands]] (July 1, 1985).

==History==
Modern U.S. state flags date from the 1890s, when states wanted to have distinctive symbols at the 1893 [[World's Columbian Exposition]] in [[Chicago|Chicago, Illinois]]. Most U.S. state flags were designed and adopted between 1893 and [[World War I]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nava.org/Flag%20Information/qa/qa8.htm |title=Questions & Answers |accessdate=2007-03-20 |last=Artimovich |first=Nick |publisher=[[North American Vexillological Association]] |pages=8 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070417172129/http://www.nava.org/Flag%20Information/qa/qa8.htm |archivedate=April 17, 2007 }}</ref>

According to a 2001 survey by the [[North American Vexillological Association]], [[New Mexico]] has the best-designed flag of any U.S. state, U.S. territory, or [[List of Canadian flags#Provincial and territorial flags|Canadian province]], while Georgia's state flag was rated the worst design.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nava.org/flag-design/survey/state-provincial-survey-2001 |title=NEW MEXICO TOPS STATE/PROVINCIAL FLAGS SURVEY, GEORGIA LOSES BY WIDE MARGIN |accessdate=2007-10-07 |last=Kaye |first=Ted |date=2001-06-10 |publisher=North American Vexillological Association |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131019210112/http://www.nava.org/flag-design/survey/state-provincial-survey-2001 |archivedate=October 19, 2013 }}</ref> (Georgia adopted a new flag in 2003; Nebraska's state flag, whose design was rated second worst, remains in use to date.)

